Forward Canvas2D ops to the bridge.

Adds an `EnsureBridgeCanvas()` helper that allocates a canvas id and
issues a `CreateCanvas2D` frame the first time a 2D op is dispatched
on a given canvas element. Each public draw method then appends a
matching op to the bridge in addition to the existing local draw.

Phase 1: ops are sent best-effort (fire-and-forget). The renderer
keeps drawing locally as before; only readback (toDataURL /
getImageData) is replaced by bridge output. This means visual display
in the page comes from local rendering, but the *bytes that JS sees*
when it reads canvas pixels come from the server. That's the only
output fpjs hashes.

A future phase can switch to "bridge owns the display image too" via
a CanvasResourceProvider variant that pulls frames from the server.

